caption: We ordered a steak and chicken quesadillas and they both were great and huge!  The salsas and guacamole were both great.  They gave us a hot pineapple salsa that was to die for, so freaking good!  I really wish this place was closer to my house in edgewater so we could order from more often.

Visited Salsita because a  friend referred me and I'm glad I did. I'm from the southside of Chicago and just moved north so I've been on the hunt for authentic tacos in the lakeview/wrigley area. Salsita didn't disappoint and they definitely gained a returning customer.
Honestly some of the best burritos in the city. Their chorizo is amazing.

We ordered a couple of vegan burritos and they were incredible! I used to order food from La Cocina all of the time and was sad to see it close due to the pandemic. However, I was so glad to find its sister restaurant Salsita and am equally if not more impressed with the food! My only concern was that my chips and salsa weren't delivered with the food and I'm hopeful that this type of mistake isn't common. It's hard to be a restaurant these days - smaller revenues, short staffing - but Salsita, please stay on the ball because you guys are good and I need you to stick around!!
Great food and great staff

On the last two occasions that we have ordered from salsita, one of us has suffered severe gastrological complications. This isn't the usual rice and beans kind of issues. Horrible diarrhea and stomach cramping. The first time it only impacted one of us, the second time, our order placed last night, hit us both today. Noticed that while we were inside the restaurant it had a horrible odor of backed up raw sewage. The salsa verde we were given with our burritos was frozen solid. The food tasted okay, but the after effects are undeniable now on this second occasion. Something is up with salsita, unsure if their food sanitation isn't up to snuff, or if there's some sort of environmental issue, but either way we won't be going back again. This makes us sad because our past experiences, before these most recent two, we're always great. For one of us it was a go-to location after being out at the bars for a long time. But whatever it is now, it's not worth the risk..
Best quesadilla I’ve ever had in my entire life
The fish tacos are really good although the hot sauce needs to be a little more spicier. The chicken quesadilla is very good with only onion and cilantro.
delicious authentic mexican food!! cash only and venmo accepted. excellent customer service and so friendly! definitely will be returning

So I’m not a fan of over-manipulating food: it should stand as it is. You can tenderize Arrachera one of two ways, either with citrus or with mechanical means. I’m not sure how they manipulate the meat but it’s perfect. It’s the perfect chew. Enough texture for the ‘mouth feel’ but none of the sinew feel. So the salsa. I grabbed two: a mango and a chipotle . The mango was light and refreshing. The chipotle was smokey and appropriately heavy. Executed perfectly! felicidades al chef Thanks, Richard Sabatini
I am impressed. I ordered fish tacos today and thought they were amazing. I am definitely going back and looking forward to trying other food items.
Tried them out for lunch today. Will definitely go again. Eating healthier just got easier

The food is amazing, but also, so are the people. I lived next door and always got a warm welcome - and in one instance, they noticed a man following me/waiting for me through their cameras and told me, waited for me to call someone, and made sure I left safely. That's not something you see every day, I was very shaken up and I appreciate it to this day a year later. Thanks salsita for the late night munchies and looking out!
Quick service and good food
My favorite taco place in the city!
The food is relatively good but the prices are pretty inflated. I only go if they have a special
Chicken tacos are very salty. Would recommend their steak or pork tacos. Tacos overall feel very pricey.

Meat options were good (nowhere near great), but the "Veggie" option, for the same price as the meat options, was literally just lettuce and sour cream. My wife didn't even ask for lettuce, but did ask for tomatoes, and didn't get them. They were cordial about getting her tomatoes, but we honestly should have just returned the tacos after she realized they were essentially just lettuce. Additionally, the salsas were meh at best.

One of the few north side locations that dishes authentic, delicious tacos and more. Been going here for years and the quality never declines. The Al Pastor is the best, but the spicy chicken is close. Highly recommend!

The people were nice, but the chicken tasted like it came out if a microwave when I was expecting a stove top. The spicy salsa was OK, but it was more like white people spicy, which is to say not very.

Food is okay! Yes, food is done quick but the issue I have is that their food is never consistent every time I go it seems like one time the food is great and the next time I am back at I will not eat this food again! I work close so it’s an quick fix for lunch but it’s one of those hit or miss situation that are little to be desired! So, in conclusion I recommend that it’s better to spend your money in a place that offers consistency, do you know you will be satisfied and happy you spent the money!
